author: EVAN GRICE Sports Editor
title: No. 17 Lady Knights crowned district champions for ninth time
text:
No. 17 Lady Knights crowned district champions for ninth time   
Since 2007, the Lindsay Lady Knights volleyball program has continued to live up to a standard of excellence in district play. 
Tuesday night at Tioga, the Lady Knights continued their dominance, as they swept the Lady Bulldogs 25-15, 25-14, 25-15, giving them a 12-0 district record and a ninth straight district championship. 
Sarah Snider led the offense with 18 kills to go with eight blocks, with Jocelyn Grewing registering 14 kills and five blocks. 
Erin Early finished with three kills and eight digs, with Makenzie Fleitman adding two kills and three digs. 
Ashley Fleitman added two kills, two blocks, seven digs and 33 assists. 
Scout Tatum added nine digs, with Morgan McClure and Sydney McCage adding four digs and two digs respectively. 
Lindsay (30-8, 12-0) will be back at Knights Gymnasium Friday afternoon against Saint Jo at 4:30 p.m. 
Whitesboro 3 Ponder 1 
Tuesday night saw the Whitesboro Lady Bearcats come up big in more ways than one. 
WHS managed to work its way to a 25-16, 22-25, 25-18, 25-21 victory over the Ponder Lady Lions, putting the Lady Bearcats just one game behind PHS with two games left on the schedule. 
Delani Dickson led the way for WHS with 16 kills and four digs on the night, with Phoenix West putting in 12 kills and eight digs. 
Lauren Purdom had nine kills and six blocks with Taylor Brown and Karlee Schuessler each putting down four kills. 
Whitesboro (22-15, 6-6) will travel to Pilot Point Friday afternoon at 4:30 p.m. 
Aubrey 3 Gainesville 0 
It was another tough night for the GHS Lady Leopards as they were swept 25-21, 25-19 and 25-10 by Aubrey at home Tuesday night. 
GHS will travel to No. 2 ranked Argyle Friday afternoon with first serve set for 4:30 p.m.
